.TH CWE-94 7 "2025-12-11" "CWE Top 25 (2025)" "Software Weakness Reference"
.SH NAME
CWE\-94 \- Improper Control of Generation of Code (Code Injection)
.SH RANK
2025 CWE Top 25 rank: \fB#10\fR (2024 rank: 11).
.SH CLASSIFICATION
Class: Injection.
.SH DESCRIPTION
The application builds code from untrusted input and then interprets/executes it, so the payload runs in the application's own language runtime \- usually full control of the process. Typical sinks are eval() and dynamic templates.
.SH MITIGATION
Never pass untrusted data to eval/exec or a general script engine. Use a purpose\-built safe parser for the intended data (a math\-expression library, a literal parser, or a data format like JSON). Keep code and data separate.
